\n|defense=133\n|fast={{m|Bite}}, {{m|Water Gun}}\n|special={{m|Surf}}, {{m|Hydro Pump}}, {{m|Crunch}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{evobox-2\n|pictype=art\n|type1=Water\n|no1=515\n|name1=Panpour\n|type1-1=Water\n|evo1={{bag|Water Stone}}<br>{{color2|000|Water Stone}}\n|no2=516\n|name2=Simipour\n|type1-2=Water}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Water}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=516}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=516}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=516}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|516|Simipour}}\n\n==Trivia==\n[[File:516Simipour old.png|thumb|Simipour\'s old artwork]]\n* Simipour represents {{wp|February}} in the [[Unova]] [[horoscope]].\n* Simipour\'s official game artwork previously showed its entire tail to be completely blue instead of tan with a blue tip.\n\n===Origin===\nSimipour is based on a {{wp|monkey}} and a {{wp|fountain}}; because of this, it may have been inspired by the water dwelling monkey-like creature {{wp|Ahuizotl (creature)|ahuizotl}}, or may be a visual pun on {{wp|Sea-Monkeys}}. The ability to store water in its hair may also reference the {{wp|Kappa (folklore)|Kappa}}, a Japanese reptilian \'\'{{wp|yōkai}}\'\' that stores water on a dish of sorts on its head. Its chest fur resembles that of a {{wp|volcano}} and may have possibly been based on {{wp|geyser}}s, {{wp|subaqueous volcano}}es, {{wp|cryovolcano}}es, or the Guatemalan {{wp|Volcán de Agua}}. Its chest fur may otherwise possibly represent the froth of a gushing {{wp|waterfall}}, with its blue locks symbolizing the waterfall.\nIt, along with its two contemporaries, seem to inspired by the {{wp|three wise monkeys}} motif; with its eyes closed, Simipour represents "see no evil".\n\n====Name origin====\nSimipour is a combination of \'\'{{wp|simian}}\'\' and \'\'pour\'\'.\n\nHiyakkie may be a combination of 冷や \'\'hiya\'\' (cool water) and \'\'{{wp|monkey}}\'\'. It may also involve けっき \'\'kekki\'\' (vigor).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Water|type2=Water\n|ja=ヒヤッキー \'\'Hiyakkie\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|冷や \'\'hiya\'\'|cool water}}, and \'\'monkey\'\'. May also involve {{tt|けっき \'\'kekki\'\'|vigor}}.\n|de=Sodachita|demeaning=From \'\'Soda\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Cheeta}}\'\'\n|fr=Flotoutan|frmeaning=From {{tt|\'\'flotte\'\'|float}} and {{tt|\'\'orang-outan\'\'|orangutan}}\n|es=Simipour|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Simipour|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=앗차키 \'\'Atchakkie\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|앗 차가워 \'\'at chagaweo\'\'|Oh, it is cold!}} and \'\'monkey\'\'\n|zh_cmn=冷水猿 \'\'Lěngshuǐyuán\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|冷水 \'\'lěngshuǐ\'\'|cold water}} and {{tt|猿 \'\'yuán\'\'|ape}}.\n|ru=Симипур \'\'Simipur\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Cress\'s Simipour]]\n* [[Elemental monkeys]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Water}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Water|prevnum=515|prev=Panpour|nextnum=517|next=Munna}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Sodachita]]\n[[es:Simipour]]\n[[fr:Flotoutan]]\n[[it:Simipour]]\n[[ja:ヒヤッキー]]\n[[zh:冷水猿]]'}